---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import Section from '../components/Section.astro';
---
<PageLayout
  title="Limitations — Syvidea"
  description="What the AMD Strix Halo / AI Max+ 395 platform is not designed for, including large-scale training, CUDA workflows, and throughput-bound image generation."
>
  <section class="relative overflow-hidden pt-20 pb-24 sm:pt-28 sm:pb-32">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-dark-999"></div>
    <div class="absolute inset-0 cyber-bg"></div>
    <div class="absolute inset-0 grid-bg opacity-20"></div>
    <div class="glow-bg top-10 left-1/3 h-96 w-96 bg-neon-orange/15 animate-glow-pulse"></div>

    <div class="container-page relative">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl text-center">
        <div class="mb-5 flex justify-center">
          <span class="badge">Honest boundaries</span>
        </div>
        <h1 class="text-balance text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight sm:text-5xl lg:text-6xl gradient-text">
          What Strix Halo is not for
        </h1>
        <p class="mx-auto mt-6 max-w-2xl text-lg text-slate-400 text-balance">
          The AMD Strix Halo / AI Max+ 395 platform is suitable for many local AI workflows, but it is not
          a universal AI machine. This page lists the main limitations so you can make an informed decision.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Section
    eyebrow="Compute limits"
    title="Not a training platform"
    align="left"
  >
    <div class="card border-neon-orange/30 bg-dark-900/60">
      <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
        Strix Halo is designed for inference, retrieval-augmented generation, agents, and multimodal
        workflows. It is not optimized for large-scale model training or fine-tuning that requires
        sustained high FLOPS over many hours.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-4 text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">
        If your workflow involves pre-training models, full fine-tuning of large models, or distributed
        training runs, a multi-GPU NVIDIA workstation or cloud cluster is typically more appropriate.
      </p>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section
    eyebrow="Ecosystem limits"
    title="Not a CUDA machine"
    align="left"
  >
    <div class="card">
      <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
        Strix Halo uses AMD integrated graphics, not NVIDIA discrete GPUs. This means CUDA and TensorRT
        are not available. Workflows built exclusively on CUDA may need to be ported to ROCm, DirectML,
        or CPU inference paths.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-4 text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">
        Many open-source tools support AMD GPUs through ROCm or Vulkan, but compatibility varies by project
        and version. The exact software stack is confirmed during the quote process.
      </p>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section
    eyebrow="Throughput limits"
    title="Not the fastest image-generation box"
    align="left"
  >
    <div class="card">
      <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
        Image generation with Flux, SDXL, and similar models is possible, but raw pixels-per-second throughput
        is lower than on an NVIDIA RTX 4090 or 5090 workstation. Strix Halo trades peak throughput for large
        unified memory capacity.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-4 text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">
        If your primary metric is maximum image-generation speed and you do not need 128 GB of unified
        memory, a dedicated NVIDIA GPU workstation is likely a better fit.
      </p>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section
    eyebrow="Practical limits"
    title="Other important boundaries"
    align="left"
  >
    <div class="grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2">
      <div class="spec-card">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-200">Memory is shared</h3>
        <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-slate-400">CPU, GPU, and NPU share 128 GB. Running multiple large models concurrently may exhaust available memory.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="spec-card">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-200">No user-upgradeable RAM</h3>
        <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-slate-400">LPDDR5X is soldered. You cannot add more RAM after purchase.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="spec-card">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-200">Software stack required</h3>
        <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-slate-400">This is not a plug-and-play appliance. Model setup, quantization, and tool configuration are required.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="spec-card">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-200">Regional availability varies</h3>
        <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-slate-400">Supply batches, certification, and shipping options vary by destination and partner brand.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Section>

</PageLayout>
